The paper discusses probabilistic treatments of neural networks, which is a topic that falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). The paper specifically focuses on computer vision (cs.CV) and mentions the use of convolutional neural networks (CNNs), which are commonly used in computer vision tasks. The paper also discusses the importance of uncertainty in neural networks, which is a topic that falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of assumed density filtering is mentioned, which is a technique commonly used in neural engineering (cs.NE). Finally, the paper discusses the robustness of the proposed probabilistic networks to adversarial examples, which is a topic that falls under the category of natural language processing (cs.CL).
